body:
Thanks for taking the time to report this.

Can you attach an example that shows the issue?  (Must be openly licensed, ideally in test_regress format.)
```verilog
interface if_1;
  bit clk;
  clocking dcb @(posedge clk);
  endclocking : dcb 
endinterface : if_1

class drv_c;
  virtual if_1 vif;

  virtual task run();
    @(vif.dcb);
  endtask : run
endclass : drv_c

module m;
  drv_c d_0;

  if_1 u_if_1 ();

  initial begin
    d_0 = new();
    d_0.vif = u_if_1;
    //d_0.run();
    $finish(2);
  end
endmodule : m


```

What 'verilator --version' are you using?  Did you try it with the git master version?

> verilator -V
> Verilator 5.013 devel rev v5.008-303-gf9164ab0d

What OS and distribution are you using?

> Windows 10, WSL

May we assist you in trying to fix this in Verilator yourself?

> Yes please. I believe it is more of UNSUPPORTED and better error messaging is the immediate "fix". Will be happy to be wrong and get VIF working though :-)
